public abstract class MediaElement
extends com.google.gwt.dom.client.Element

Abstract element that supports media playback.

play

public final void play()
Sets the paused attribute to false, loading the media resource and beginning playback if necessary. If the playback had ended, will restart it from the start.

setAutobuffer

public final void setAutobuffer(boolean autobuffer)
Sets whether autobuffer is used. If true, hints to the user agent that the author believes that the media element will likely be used, even though the element does not have an autoplay attribute. This attribute may be ignored altogether. The attribute must be ignored if the autoplay attribute is present.

Parameters:
autobuffer -

setAutoplay

public final void setAutoplay(boolean autoplay)
If true, the user agent will automatically begin playback of the media resource as soon as it can do so without stopping.

setControls

public final void setControls(boolean controls)
If true, it indicates that the author has not provided a scripted controller and would like the user agent to provide its own set of controls.

setCurrentTime

public final void setCurrentTime(float currentTime)
Sets the current playback position, expressed in seconds.

setDefaultPlaybackRate

public final void setDefaultPlaybackRate(float defaultPlaybackRate)
Sets the desired speed at which the media resource is to play, as a multiple of its intrinsic speed. Default: 1

setLoop

public final void setLoop(boolean loop)
If true, indicates that the media element is to seek back to the start of the media resource upon reaching the end.

setMuted

public final void setMuted(boolean muted)
If true, the audio channels are muted.

setPlaybackRate

public final void setPlaybackRate(float playbackRate)
Sets the speed at which the media resource plays, as a multiple of its intrinsic speed. If it is not equal to the defaultPlaybackRate, then the implication is that the user is using a feature such as fast forward or slow motion playback. Default: 1
